1
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:40,540
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,970
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:46,210
(Episode 15)

4
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:03,460
(Missed Call)

5
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:04,630
(New Message)

6
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:05,770
(Missed Call)

7
00:01:05,830 --> 00:01:06,970
(New Message)

8
00:01:07,030 --> 00:01:08,170
(New Message)

9
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:15,070
(Messages)

10
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:18,380
(Director Shin, please text me
when you have a moment. Ba Ra.)

11
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:24,620
Director Shin, please text me
when you have a moment.

12
00:01:25,180 --> 00:01:26,190
Ba Ra.

13
00:01:32,730 --> 00:01:34,190
Hello, Director Shin.

14
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:38,300
- Where are you?
- I'm at the cafe by the hospital.

15
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:42,140
- You're at the cafe now?
- Yes. But...

16
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:46,610
I'd like to meet somewhere quiet.
It's a little noisy here.

17
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:49,510
Go on up to my place.
The door code is the same.

18
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:55,050
Did you forget? Want me to text it to you?

19
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,680
No.

20
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:21,770
You've been in Korea?

21
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:24,210
- Yes.
- But...

22
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:26,850
where?

23
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:31,620
I'll order something.

24
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:33,690
You haven't had dinner, have you?

25
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,350
I'm not hungry.

26
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,790
Should I make you something simple?

27
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:53,070
Did you get married?

28
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:54,940
No.

29
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:58,910
(Someone said they saw you...)

30
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,580
About the surgery you mentioned before...

31
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,520
I'll do it.

32
00:03:07,350 --> 00:03:08,350
Please do it for me.

33
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:18,430
Do you want me to explain why?

34
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,970
- Change?
- Yes.

35
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:27,840
- Momo might not agree to it.
- Even if she doesn't.

36
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:33,080
I'll take full responsibility.

37
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,450
Are you not up for it?

38
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:55,900
All right.

39
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:06,210
(Nua General Hospital)

40
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:32,340
Have a seat.

41
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:46,090
I rushed over...

42
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:47,820
empty-handed.

43
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,160
Are you okay?

44
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:57,200
I just had a dizzy spell.

45
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,200
You still look good.

46
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:06,740
I do?

47
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:11,440
I saw Momo. She said she's happy.

48
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:15,720
Except that you're
a bit too obsessed with her.

49
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,120
That's why she's deliberately...

50
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,820
keeping her distance for a while.

51
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:27,730
We decided to get a divorce.

52
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,160
We're going to.

53
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,400
How could you just leave like that?

54
00:05:39,470 --> 00:05:41,870
- Vertigo?
- I have a blood test tomorrow.

55
00:05:42,410 --> 00:05:43,710
They think it might be anemia.

56
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:45,410
So you have to fast tonight?

57
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,680
I'm not really that hungry.

58
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:50,650
Why are you being so formal?

59
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,750
You're not even looking at me.

60
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:03,360
Did something happen?

61
00:06:07,030 --> 00:06:08,030
No.

62
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:10,370
Someone...

63
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,140
said they saw you at a rest stop.

64
00:06:13,810 --> 00:06:15,140
You were with an elderly woman.

65
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:18,810
That was probably me.

66
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:24,750
Did you meet someone?

67
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,760
I said I needed time back then.

68
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,690
Time to force feelings for you?

69
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,200
I wasn't forcing it.

70
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:43,300
Will you keep on staying at a distance?

71
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,140
My feelings haven't changed.

72
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,320
Nothing's changed.

73
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,220
We should have been honest...

74
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,160
and talked everything out sooner.

75
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:16,270
- What about a caregiver?
- I don't need one.

76
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,770
I can still get around on my own.

77
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:19,870
Then I'll stay with you.

78
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:21,840
As Momo's world-famous husband?

79
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:25,710
You're angry with me,

80
00:07:26,450 --> 00:07:27,510
aren't you?

81
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,190
I lost sight of the young girl
you used to be.

82
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:35,920
I didn't even make an effort.

83
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:40,360
Please, stop being upset.

84
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,070
I'm here to check your blood pressure.

85
00:07:46,770 --> 00:07:47,830
You can go now.

86
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:54,410
Your number.

87
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:17,660
I'll do anything to convince Ba Ra,

88
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,300
so please do the surgery again.

89
00:08:20,130 --> 00:08:22,470
Just turn me into Ba Ra,
and then we can get married.

90
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:26,370
Ba Ra showed up today.

91
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:28,310
I met her.

92
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,540
What did she say?

93
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:35,710
I'll have ten kids
if that's what it takes.

94
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,320
As many as we can have.

95
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:42,920
I know Ba Ra,
and Yong Joong is the only one for her.

96
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:45,460
And after Geum Ba Ra disappeared,

97
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,690
Ha Yong Joong couldn't stop
thinking about her either.

98
00:08:48,430 --> 00:08:50,700
We don't have to live as a couple
in name only anymore.

99
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,470
I want to do something good for once.

100
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:06,450
Ba Ra can become Momo
and marry Yong Joong,

101
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,180
and I'll become Ba Ra...

102
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:11,580
and live my life
admiring and devoted to you.

103
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:14,450
I'll study hard to become
more cultured and refined.

104
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,760
It's a win-win for everyone.

105
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,600
Discuss it with Ba Ra.

106
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:28,830
If she agrees to switch,

107
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:30,500
will you really do it?

108
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:41,610
I can put everything I just said
in writing as a pledge.

109
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:48,190
The truth is,
the news articles were right.

110
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,190
Things aren't good
between Yong Joong and me.

111
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:53,390
I just pretended
we were fine out of pride.

112
00:09:55,230 --> 00:09:59,030
Think about becoming Momo
and marrying Yong Joong.

113
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:06,510
And I could become you
and live as Geum Ba Ra.

114
00:10:08,270 --> 00:10:11,610
And I could become you
and live as Geum Ba Ra.

115
00:10:13,610 --> 00:10:16,220
Director Shin said he'd do the surgery
if you agreed.

116
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:19,890
You'll get wealth, fame, and even love,

117
00:10:20,290 --> 00:10:22,790
all from a surgery that takes a few hours.

118
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:29,430
Director Shin is an amazing surgeon.

119
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:31,500
I was completely blown away.

120
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:37,870
No matter how good Director Shin is to you
or how hard he tries,

121
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,310
you have no intention
of marrying him, right?

122
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:45,080
Honestly, don't you feel a little bad
for Director Shin?

123
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,780
He seems to have it all,
but when you really think about it,

124
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,520
does he have time to spend his money?

125
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,380
Or does he really have
any hobbies he enjoys?

126
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:55,550
He's in this hospital 24 hours a day,

127
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:58,720
either in the OR, his office,
or a patient's room.

128
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:03,060
If I became you
and married Director Shin...

129
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:05,830
and then dedicated my life
to taking proper care of him,

130
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,130
wouldn't that give you
more peace of mind, too?

131
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:14,940
Why did things go bad
between you and Yong Joong?

132
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,410
A little bit of everything, I guess.

133
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,150
We're completely incompatible,

134
00:11:20,210 --> 00:11:21,350
right down to our tastes.

135
00:11:22,110 --> 00:11:23,880
I think he was just Momo's fan.

136
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:27,320
You're sick and tired of your life, too,
aren't you?

137
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,260
Think of the discrimination and neglect
we grew up with.

138
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,260
Don't you have any intention
of apologizing to me?

139
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,630
Not even now?

140
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:45,340
For what?

141
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:48,010
I want an apology. A proper one.

142
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:50,480
I deserve one.

143
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:58,750
My life could have been so much better
if it weren't for you.

144
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,550
But you ruined everything.

145
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,820
By framing me for theft.

146
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:09,160
Even now, my chest gets tight
just thinking about it.

147
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:10,830
If you were in my shoes,

148
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,470
how would you have felt
if I'd done that to you?

149
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:21,570
I'm sorry.

150
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:24,410
I kept hoping
you would apologize eventually.

151
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:29,080
Since we were both left in the baby box
on the same day and grew up together,

152
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,380
I decided to just let it slide.

153
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:33,920
But you acted like nothing ever happened.

154
00:12:35,450 --> 00:12:37,320
You weren't the Kim Jin Ju
I thought I knew.

155
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:40,630
I don't know how a person
could do something like that.

156
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:43,900
You act nice, then stab me in the back.

157
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,360
I didn't stab you in the back.

158
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,370
You didn't?

159
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,640
My circumstances made me that way.

160
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:57,880
- You don't get it?
- No.

161
00:12:58,210 --> 00:13:00,050
We had the exact same circumstances.

162
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:04,320
That's because you're smart.

163
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:07,350
This isn't about being smart.
It's about having a conscience.

164
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,790
You ended up fine even though
Ye Jeong's family didn't adopt you.

165
00:13:14,290 --> 00:13:16,500
But I was more heartbroken
than anyone else.

166
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:20,300
To be betrayed by you, of all people.

167
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,900
But I paid for it in the end.

168
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,840
I was wrong.

169
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:29,170
I'm sorry.

170
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:35,150
Deep down, I was always sorry.

171
00:13:36,580 --> 00:13:38,680
But you were always so cold to me,

172
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,320
I could never bring myself to say it.

173
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:44,290
Living as Momo can't be that bad.

174
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:46,690
So what if you get divorced?

175
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:50,460
You can meet any rich, famous guy
you want.

176
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,430
Why do you want to become me?

177
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,170
My pride.

178
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,640
Everyone would love to see me fail,
wouldn't they?

179
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:02,770
The haters, the reporters...

180
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:06,250
You know how many reporters
can't stand Momo.

181
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:09,110
You'd do the surgery again just for that?

182
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,820
It's only the first step that's hard.

183
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,020
You're just asleep for a few hours,
and then you wake up.

184
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:14,620
It's no big deal.

185
00:14:18,590 --> 00:14:20,690
Try living as Momo for a while.

186
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,790
Spending money is a lot of fun, too.

187
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,430
It's beyond your wildest dreams.

188
00:14:27,230 --> 00:14:31,800
There's no reason
to cling to that face and body.

189
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:36,440
Think of all the tears you've shed
with those eyes.

190
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:40,780
Fate gives everyone a few chances in life.

191
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,410
Think of this as one of them.

192
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:47,350
Ever since you disappeared,
I've lived with a shell of Ha Yong Joong.

193
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:50,020
I can't do it anymore.
I'm sick and tired of it.

194
00:14:52,090 --> 00:14:54,190
Director Shin might seem cold
on the outside,

195
00:14:55,090 --> 00:14:57,560
but he's better than the empty shell
Ha Yong Joong has become.

196
00:14:57,830 --> 00:14:59,000
Even if he only wants Ba Ra's body.

197
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,940
It's about choosing the next-best thing.

198
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,840
That's what Director Shin is doing.

199
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:07,370
And Ha Yong Joong
has to pay the price, too.

200
00:15:08,010 --> 00:15:12,380
He doesn't deserve to marry the real you.
Didn't he just end up hurting us both?

201
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,510
He should've chosen you from the start.

202
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:20,090
Do you need some time to think?

203
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,460
I should've listened to you.

204
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:31,360
There's no turning back now.

205
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:34,200
Everyone makes mistakes. We're human.

206
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:35,930
Just as long as you don't repeat them.

207
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,270
Chalk it up to a life lesson.

208
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:43,510
By the way,

209
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,640
Momo is a world-class liar.

210
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:48,010
Saying she was abused growing up?

211
00:15:49,410 --> 00:15:50,880
Just what you'd expect from an actress.

212
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:52,850
Hyun Ran Hee.

213
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:56,490
After her first love,
Paul, the artist, came to Korea,

214
00:15:56,490 --> 00:15:58,420
she found out
she had lost her own daughter.

215
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,660
So what's all this about abuse?

216
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:03,860
She thought her daughter was living well
in Japan with Paul.

217
00:16:06,330 --> 00:16:07,530
I'm going to finalize the paperwork,

218
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:10,340
and then I'm going to marry Ba Ra.

219
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:13,710
You found Reporter Geum?

220
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:18,080
Please check the baby's diaper often.
The baby is very sensitive.

221
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,780
Is Grandmother still eating well?

222
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:31,620
She especially likes hairtail,
so make sure to debone it well for her.

223
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:35,760
Okay.

224
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:37,900
Her hemoglobin levels are a bit low,

225
00:16:38,660 --> 00:16:40,270
but that can happen to women
because of their period.

226
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:43,070
But just in case,
I've scheduled an MRI this weekend.

227
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:45,140
Does she just need to eat well?
Things like meat?

228
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,040
Well, she's on an albumin drip for now.

229
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,910
Did she say anything else?

230
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:54,150
Like how she's been?

231
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,420
She'll talk when she's ready.

232
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,690
(Ready for surgery)

233
00:17:00,850 --> 00:17:02,020
I have to go into surgery.

234
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:09,830
(No Visitors Permitted,
Please inquire at the nurses' station.)

235
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:26,210
It says no visitors.

236
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,370
Let's finalize everything in six months.

237
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,470
That's if you haven't changed
your mind by then.

238
00:17:54,270 --> 00:17:57,340
I know I haven't been my best self.

239
00:17:57,610 --> 00:17:59,680
I've been on edge
and took it out on you a lot.

240
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,050
I know I didn't live up to
your expectations.

241
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,150
I just want to stay your wife
for a few more months,

242
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:10,920
even if it's only on paper.

243
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:15,130
You don't have to give me alimony.
I didn't mean what I said.

244
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,460
I know money can't make up for it,

245
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:21,970
but you should take what you're owed.

246
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:27,640
If I hadn't had the miscarriage,
we probably would've just made it work.

247
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,780
I'll get the rest of my stuff tomorrow.

248
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:40,320
Ask Geum Ba Ra if she was really pregnant.

249
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:42,490
Someone saw her, and you can't even ask?

250
00:18:55,230 --> 00:18:56,230
Are you sleeping?

251
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:23,060
(New Message)

252
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,070
Can we meet tomorrow?

253
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:35,610
I can't eat since I'm fasting.

254
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,120
Like Director Shin said,

255
00:19:53,390 --> 00:19:55,090
it's true that
I used to have feelings for you.

256
00:19:56,700 --> 00:20:00,500
When I was younger,
I just liked you because you doted on me.

257
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:08,470
I guess feelings are like the wind.

258
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:11,040
Over the past year,

259
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,510
those feelings have faded.

260
00:20:14,010 --> 00:20:15,410
All that was left behind
were the memories.

261
00:20:16,820 --> 00:20:17,980
The good ones.

262
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,620
You've given me so many.

263
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,250
We made them together.

264
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,060
Now, I'm the one...

265
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:27,630
who's going to like you much more.

266
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:31,200
I'm the one who messed everything up...

267
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:33,770
because I was so foolish.

268
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:37,700
I guess people need someone
to pour their heart into.

269
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,910
For me, that person was you.

270
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:44,580
But that's not the case anymore,
so don't feel burdened.

271
00:20:47,550 --> 00:20:48,950
Are you going to keep pushing me away?

272
00:20:52,450 --> 00:20:54,720
I understand if you're disappointed in me,
if you've lost all feelings for me.

273
00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:56,190
I would be too.

274
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,630
I just didn't realize
how I felt soon enough.

275
00:21:01,890 --> 00:21:02,960
Please understand.

276
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:14,540
Could you even accept...

277
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:18,010
my child?

278
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,790
I won't ask about the circumstances.

279
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:35,660
Of course.

280
00:21:36,330 --> 00:21:38,660
If the baby is yours,
then they're precious and dear to me too.

281
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:43,670
I really mean it.

282
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:47,310
You're here in front of me right now.

283
00:21:50,540 --> 00:21:51,910
And you're looking at me.

284
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:53,850
That's all that matters.

285
00:21:56,820 --> 00:21:58,820
I never thought
I'd have this moment again.

286
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:04,120
That phrase, "aching with longing"...

287
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,620
I thought it was just
a line in a pop song.

288
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:09,360
But that's exactly how I felt.

289
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:14,070
It was torture.

290
00:22:15,130 --> 00:22:16,470
I feel bad for Momo, but...

291
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:25,980
Thank you.

292
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:30,720
I was so pathetic...

293
00:22:31,780 --> 00:22:33,050
and completely clueless.

294
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:36,050
It's not that you were clueless.

295
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:39,290
It's just that Momo completely occupied...

296
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:41,360
your heart.

297
00:22:42,390 --> 00:22:45,260
You know that saying, "Blinded by greed."

298
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:47,630
It wasn't love.

299
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,200
I just got swept away for a moment...

300
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:53,410
by the actress, Momo.

301
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,580
I know I've sinned against both of you,

302
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,050
but please look kindly on me.

303
00:23:01,910 --> 00:23:03,550
I'm asking just this once.

304
00:23:07,490 --> 00:23:08,490
Now,

305
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,990
I think I'm starting to get
a faint idea of what love is...

306
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:13,320
and what it's supposed to be.

307
00:23:15,860 --> 00:23:17,260
But people say love changes.

308
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:19,960
Love is different from a simple feeling.

309
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:21,830
Feelings are what come and go.

310
00:23:25,940 --> 00:23:28,040
I finally get just how hard and painful
it must have been for you,

311
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:32,210
now that I'm experiencing it myself.

312
00:23:41,990 --> 00:23:44,160
Let's just say we both messed up
because we were immature,

313
00:23:46,690 --> 00:23:48,090
and let's start over.

314
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:51,300
The right way, for real this time.

315
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:00,100
Things with Momo will be over
in a few months.

316
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:03,070
I promised.

317
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,650
When did you have the baby?

318
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:11,480
Where is the baby now?
Who's taking care of it?

319
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:18,360
You can tell me when you want to.
When you're ready.

320
00:24:18,620 --> 00:24:21,330
- What's important is...
- Remember what I say now.

321
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:26,130
I don't regret...

322
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,630
loving you.

323
00:24:29,130 --> 00:24:30,440
I have never once regretted it.

324
00:24:31,540 --> 00:24:34,440
The truth is,
I loved you more than words can say.

325
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:39,780
And now?

326
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:46,220
Thank you.

327
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:49,890
Remember what I'm about
to say to you now too.

328
00:24:52,390 --> 00:24:55,030
Ha Yong Joong will never
leave Geum Ba Ra again.

329
00:24:59,530 --> 00:25:00,930
And I'll make sure of it.

330
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,040
Let's watch our hair turn gray...

331
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,840
and see each other grow old.

332
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:10,580
Let's live a long, long life together.

333
00:26:16,370 --> 00:26:19,540
Do you really think you can be happy,
Ha Yong Joong, after making me cry?

334
00:26:20,210 --> 00:26:22,350
I'm going to make your life
a living torment.

335
00:26:23,210 --> 00:26:26,120
I'm not the Kim Jin Ju who was impressed
by your 100-dollar taxi fare anymore.

336
00:26:35,730 --> 00:26:36,730
Can I help you?

337
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:41,730
The card...

338
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:43,940
I'm just here for a delivery.

339
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:45,800
Which unit?

340
00:26:46,540 --> 00:26:48,070
Unit 701, for Momo.

341
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:51,480
You can't just leave it here.
Take it up to her front door.

342
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,480
Her helper already went home for the day.

343
00:26:55,310 --> 00:26:57,020
Then buzz me in.

344
00:27:46,460 --> 00:27:47,530
Drive.

345
00:27:47,930 --> 00:27:49,500
- You scream, and you'll regret it!
- Dad!

346
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,470
It's me, Jin Ju.

347
00:27:54,670 --> 00:27:57,340
I'm Momo now! We swapped brains!

348
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:00,310
Don't give me that crap.

349
00:28:01,250 --> 00:28:03,610
If you don't believe me,
the surgery scar is on my head.

350
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:12,190
Where is it?

351
00:28:23,330 --> 00:28:24,340
Proof.

352
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:27,070
The surgery scar is the proof, Dad.

353
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:28,910
Front door code...

354
00:28:29,510 --> 00:28:30,610
to your house.

355
00:28:32,010 --> 00:28:33,380
Which one? Hyeonmi Villa?

356
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,610
What was the code again?

357
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:38,550
It's 3-5-4-4!

358
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,520
Kim Jin Ju's bank account balance.

359
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,920
It was probably 10,500 dollars.

360
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:44,990
Bank...

361
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:47,660
- account number.
- Shinjun Bank.

362
00:28:47,930 --> 00:28:51,560
It's 222-812058-03014.

363
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:58,040
- Drive.
- Where to?

364
00:28:58,340 --> 00:29:00,640
Home. Hyeonmi Villa.

365
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:07,610
Don't try anything funny.
I've got nothing to lose.

366
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:11,450
I won't, Dad.

367
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,150
The Han River Park.

368
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,150
Not home?

369
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:25,930
So only your brain is Jin Ju's?

370
00:29:27,170 --> 00:29:28,170
Yes.

371
00:29:29,030 --> 00:29:30,200
Then what about the body?

372
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:33,040
What happened to Jin Ju's body?

373
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:34,710
I don't know.

374
00:29:35,810 --> 00:29:37,440
I can't drive, Dad.

375
00:29:37,710 --> 00:29:38,880
It's a long story.

376
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,850
Can you put that away?

377
00:29:42,610 --> 00:29:43,650
I'm shaking too much.

378
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,790
Is that even possible?

379
00:29:55,990 --> 00:29:57,800
It is, that's why I'm here just fine...

380
00:30:03,370 --> 00:30:04,670
How did you know, Dad?

381
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:06,040
The earring.

382
00:30:07,670 --> 00:30:08,710
My earring?

383
00:30:08,710 --> 00:30:10,170
The one with the pearl.

384
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,540
How could I forget?
Your mother bought it for you.

385
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,110
It was the first gift I ever gave a woman.

386
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:18,150
I saw it a few days ago
at Director Shin's hospital...

387
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:19,780
when you took photos with your fans.

388
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:21,720
Dad, you were there?

389
00:30:22,050 --> 00:30:23,050
So...

390
00:30:25,220 --> 00:30:26,290
your body...

391
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,860
is just gone?

392
00:30:34,470 --> 00:30:35,530
How could...

393
00:30:36,900 --> 00:30:38,100
That bastard Director Shin.

394
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,170
Director Shin isn't at fault here.

395
00:30:40,170 --> 00:30:42,340
There are certain lines you don't cross.

396
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:47,510
Did you ask for this,

397
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:49,050
or were you offered it?

398
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:54,150
- You wretched girl!
- Dad!

399
00:30:54,150 --> 00:30:55,750
Don't you call me Dad.

400
00:30:57,860 --> 00:30:59,290
To cut ties with your own father,

401
00:31:00,630 --> 00:31:02,530
you'd go as far as killing your own body.

402
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:04,360
I was scared.

403
00:31:06,130 --> 00:31:07,430
Scared of your own father?

404
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:10,070
What did I ever do to you?

405
00:31:10,130 --> 00:31:11,270
It's just...

406
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:14,240
I was sick and tired of everything.

407
00:31:15,010 --> 00:31:16,310
It wasn't really because of you.

408
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:17,610
Then...

409
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,480
why didn't you tell me after the surgery?

410
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:24,720
If the world found out, I'd be finished.

411
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:27,220
I was going to come find you
once things blew over.

412
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:29,220
I swear.

413
00:31:32,890 --> 00:31:35,660
And living as Momo hasn't been easy.

414
00:31:35,730 --> 00:31:37,430
Why are you and Ha Yong Joong separated?

415
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,930
- We just drifted apart.
- Who did?

416
00:31:43,730 --> 00:31:46,040
- Both of us.
- You sure he didn't figure it out?

417
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:47,940
It's more complicated than that.

418
00:31:48,210 --> 00:31:50,010
It was just a lot of things piling up.

419
00:31:57,180 --> 00:31:58,220
Wire me some money.

420
00:31:59,220 --> 00:32:00,250
Send one big one for now.

421
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:01,750
A thousand dollars?

422
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:03,920
Ten thousand dollars?

423
00:32:05,420 --> 00:32:07,730
Is a big one, only 10,000 dollars
for someone like Momo?

424
00:32:09,590 --> 00:32:12,200
The daily limit is 50,000 dollars.

425
00:32:13,100 --> 00:32:15,270
Then send
the other 50,000 dollars tomorrow.

426
00:32:15,270 --> 00:32:17,300
Then wire 200,000 dollars by the weekend.

427
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:18,970
Go to the bank in person if you have to.

428
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:27,010
After severing family ties like that,

429
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:29,050
did you really think you could be happy?

430
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:30,850
The sky...

431
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:33,220
will punish you.

432
00:32:36,090 --> 00:32:37,090
Woosung Bank.

433
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:39,120
Account 5-2-5...

434
00:32:41,790 --> 00:32:43,230
I don't have any beer.

435
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:44,300
Will a Coke do?

436
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:45,560
Then...

437
00:32:47,470 --> 00:32:48,500
Liquor.

438
00:32:49,030 --> 00:32:50,230
Whiskey.

439
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:52,040
Give me the key card too.

440
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:21,870
Aren't you hot?
Why are you still wearing that?

441
00:33:22,370 --> 00:33:23,600
I have a bit of a cold.

442
00:33:23,730 --> 00:33:25,700
The code to Director Shin's penthouse.

443
00:33:28,370 --> 00:33:31,880
- Why?
- So I know. Stop asking questions.

444
00:33:49,330 --> 00:33:50,630
After you two break up,

445
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,300
should I ask Director Shin...

446
00:33:54,130 --> 00:33:56,300
to turn me into Ha Yong Joong?

447
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:01,070
How much does it hurt?

448
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:06,280
You can't go through that twice, Dad.

449
00:34:09,050 --> 00:34:10,050
Is that...

450
00:34:10,050 --> 00:34:11,220
Sonbeni?

451
00:35:06,540 --> 00:35:08,210
(Nua General Hospital)

452
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,180
Are you nervous?

453
00:35:15,250 --> 00:35:16,280
Don't worry.

454
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,990
I might treat you coldly.

455
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,720
But you'll have Momo's face.

456
00:35:39,170 --> 00:35:40,400
Just relax.

457
00:35:41,210 --> 00:35:42,240
And try to get some sleep.

458
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,200
Oh my gosh!

459
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:56,910
- How did you get in here?
- What do you mean?

460
00:37:57,270 --> 00:37:59,340
You gave me the key card.

461
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,050
Who did?

462
00:38:01,450 --> 00:38:02,550
Playing dumb again?

463
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:03,880
It's just...

464
00:38:06,020 --> 00:38:07,150
By any chance,

465
00:38:07,850 --> 00:38:09,450
did you get it from Jin Ju?

466
00:38:10,620 --> 00:38:12,120
You changed the passcode, didn't you?

467
00:38:13,060 --> 00:38:14,120
Open up.

468
00:38:14,860 --> 00:38:16,390
Should I just spill everything?

469
00:38:16,390 --> 00:38:18,360
A strange man keeps ringing my doorbell.

470
00:38:18,430 --> 00:38:21,000
Please come quickly.
Noir Hospital, 21st floor.

471
00:38:21,900 --> 00:38:22,900
Yes.

472
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,250
What about Ba Ra?

473
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:56,730
Ma'am!

474
00:39:17,890 --> 00:39:19,020
It's Mommy.

475
00:39:19,990 --> 00:39:21,090
Remember me, okay?

476
00:39:23,460 --> 00:39:25,230
I'll come back safe and sound...

477
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:27,700
and give my baby boy many hugs.

478
00:39:28,830 --> 00:39:30,230
Eat well,

479
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:32,540
and sleep well.

480
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:46,350
I love you.

481
00:39:48,690 --> 00:39:50,420
I love you, my sweet baby.

482
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,700
(New Message, Actress Momo)

483
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:42,540
Reporter Geum Ba Ra,
is this a good time to talk?

484
00:40:46,980 --> 00:40:48,450
(Actress Momo)

485
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,450
Hello, Ms. Geum.

486
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:56,120
Momo.

487
00:40:56,490 --> 00:40:59,890
I'm at my villa having some wine.

488
00:41:01,430 --> 00:41:02,760
With friends?

489
00:41:03,290 --> 00:41:05,460
No, I'm alone.

490
00:41:06,730 --> 00:41:08,830
And I found myself thinking of you.

491
00:41:09,370 --> 00:41:11,100
The look in your eyes, to be exact.

492
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:14,200
Was the look in my eyes...

493
00:41:15,140 --> 00:41:16,410
bad?

494
00:41:16,870 --> 00:41:18,310
I'll tell you when you get here.

495
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:21,650
Where is your villa?

496
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:24,980
If you text me your address,
I'll send my manager.

497
00:41:25,050 --> 00:41:26,080
He'll give you a ride here.

498
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,190
The buses don't come out this far.

499
00:42:08,030 --> 00:42:09,030
Goodness.

500
00:42:10,330 --> 00:42:11,330
Go ahead, take it.

501
00:42:14,330 --> 00:42:17,470
Director, if it's not urgent,
can I call you back?

502
00:42:17,830 --> 00:42:18,840
Okay.

503
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:22,010
I'm sorry you have to see me like this.

504
00:42:23,770 --> 00:42:25,040
Is something wrong?

505
00:42:25,740 --> 00:42:28,610
No, I really was just thinking of you.

506
00:42:29,310 --> 00:42:31,420
And I'm sorry to bother you
on your day off.

507
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:35,150
Are you kidding?
An invitation from you is an honor.

508
00:42:35,220 --> 00:42:37,220
Since we met at that
Japanese restaurant by chance,

509
00:42:37,220 --> 00:42:40,020
I think about the look in your eyes.

510
00:42:40,590 --> 00:42:42,990
It was so indifferent, I guess?

511
00:42:45,330 --> 00:42:47,500
You didn't see me as Momo the actress.

512
00:42:47,500 --> 00:42:49,630
You saw me as a regular person.

513
00:42:50,700 --> 00:42:52,740
I figured you'd be uncomfortable
if I made a big deal out of it.

514
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:54,270
Exactly.

515
00:42:55,370 --> 00:42:59,510
To put it a bit dramatically,

516
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:02,480
unlike how people's eyes pounce on me,

517
00:43:03,050 --> 00:43:04,780
you were a breath of fresh air.

518
00:43:05,820 --> 00:43:07,820
You made me feel at ease, and I liked it.

519
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:10,720
That's a relief.
I'm glad you took it that way.

520
00:43:10,950 --> 00:43:13,520
You were putting yourself in my shoes,
weren't you?

521
00:43:14,860 --> 00:43:16,660
I know what it's like for actors.

522
00:43:16,990 --> 00:43:18,930
You're constantly hounded by people.

523
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:22,230
I'm sure it's something
to be grateful for.

524
00:43:22,530 --> 00:43:24,700
A lot of times, it can be overwhelming.

525
00:43:30,210 --> 00:43:31,780
Could you be like a big sister to me?

526
00:43:32,240 --> 00:43:34,010
Treat me like your little sister.

527
00:43:36,410 --> 00:43:37,650
Do you have any younger siblings?

528
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:40,180
I'm an only child, too.

529
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:43,690
Weren't you ever jealous of friends
who had older siblings?

530
00:43:45,190 --> 00:43:47,460
But at least you have your parents, Momo.

531
00:43:48,030 --> 00:43:49,790
I grew up in an orphanage.

532
00:43:50,390 --> 00:43:52,900
Goodness, I had no idea.

533
00:43:54,830 --> 00:43:58,940
I'm used to people being taken aback
with that expression.

534
00:43:59,770 --> 00:44:03,970
I'm not taken aback.
I assumed you grew up with a silver spoon.

535
00:44:04,140 --> 00:44:05,580
You just give off that vibe.

536
00:44:07,110 --> 00:44:08,150
I do?

537
00:44:08,850 --> 00:44:11,580
That makes you even more amazing.
That sobered me right up.

538
00:44:15,290 --> 00:44:18,990
I was going to vent,
but I'd rather hear your story instead.

539
00:44:19,220 --> 00:44:21,160
I'm not just being nosy.

540
00:44:21,290 --> 00:44:22,560
There's not much to tell.

541
00:44:23,260 --> 00:44:27,030
Orphanages these days are a lot nicer
than you'd think.

542
00:44:43,550 --> 00:44:45,320
Oh, you made gimbap?

543
00:44:45,550 --> 00:44:48,390
I was in the middle of making some
when you called.

544
00:44:49,050 --> 00:44:51,590
But we don't have any fruit.
I should've bought some.

545
00:44:51,590 --> 00:44:52,920
That's okay. We don't need any.

546
00:44:53,290 --> 00:44:54,490
I have plenty of snacks instead.

547
00:45:05,170 --> 00:45:06,640
Gosh, this is amazing.

548
00:45:06,700 --> 00:45:09,010
I've never had gimbap like this before.

549
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:10,970
It's aged kimchi gimbap.

550
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:13,540
I just threw it together with what I had.

551
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:16,280
Aged kimchi makes it taste so...

552
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,650
It's so clean, yet so flavorful.

553
00:45:20,020 --> 00:45:21,250
You probably shouldn't gain weight.

554
00:45:21,250 --> 00:45:22,690
I'll just starve myself tomorrow.

555
00:45:23,420 --> 00:45:24,960
Fasting is just part of the job.

556
00:45:30,530 --> 00:45:31,960
It must be stressful, right?

557
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:36,300
From what I see,
actors lose just as much as they gain.

558
00:45:36,570 --> 00:45:39,870
That reporter, Lee Si Kyung,
is out for my blood.

559
00:45:40,170 --> 00:45:41,710
Does he really hate me that much?

560
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:44,940
- You saw the articles, right?
- Think of him as your nemesis.

561
00:45:45,080 --> 00:45:46,640
We all have one.

562
00:45:48,010 --> 00:45:49,980
For me, the world itself was my nemesis.

563
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:52,620
I must sound pathetic,
whining in front of you.

564
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:55,150
I'm not judging.
If anything, I understand you better.

565
00:45:55,250 --> 00:45:59,390
There's this very popular veteran actress.
We were in a show together.

566
00:45:59,990 --> 00:46:03,030
She kept saying how unique and pretty
my bag was and asked me for it,

567
00:46:03,290 --> 00:46:06,230
but I told her I couldn't
since a fan made it for me.

568
00:46:07,230 --> 00:46:09,500
Since then, she's been bad-mouthing me.

569
00:46:09,630 --> 00:46:10,670
You're kidding.

570
00:46:10,670 --> 00:46:14,240
Saying I have the worst attitude
and that I don't even say hello.

571
00:46:14,670 --> 00:46:16,310
But I've never even left her on read.

572
00:46:17,970 --> 00:46:20,940
She's raising two daughters of her own.
How can she act like that?

573
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:23,780
What if her daughters go out in the world
and someone treats them the same way?

574
00:46:25,550 --> 00:46:27,820
The world doesn't run on common sense.

575
00:46:27,820 --> 00:46:29,250
And people aren't always what you expect.

576
00:46:29,820 --> 00:46:31,090
I think...

577
00:46:31,450 --> 00:46:34,690
the world has half and half.
Half are good, and half are bad.

578
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:39,300
Will evil people ever just disappear?

579
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:42,230
The world has no use for them.

580
00:46:42,230 --> 00:46:43,800
They'll never go away.

581
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:47,000
The universe has day and night, right?

582
00:46:47,400 --> 00:46:49,240
As long as the universe exists,

583
00:46:49,240 --> 00:46:52,480
the human world, just like day and night,
will have good people and bad people.

584
00:46:54,340 --> 00:46:56,180
You just have to accept it for what it is.

585
00:46:56,580 --> 00:46:59,250
As long as we're not the evil ones
hurting others,

586
00:46:59,520 --> 00:47:01,620
we can take comfort in that
and be at peace.

587
00:47:03,250 --> 00:47:04,450
Is it that easy for you?

588
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:09,130
I've been slandered and had my share
of hard times, too.

589
00:47:09,430 --> 00:47:11,060
But at some point, it just clicked.

590
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,830
They say humans mirror the universe...

591
00:47:13,830 --> 00:47:16,670
I guess it’s the same principle,
the same phenomenon...

592
00:47:17,530 --> 00:47:21,710
I realized I shouldn't get caught up in it
and just stick to my own path.

593
00:47:27,780 --> 00:47:29,080
You're so right.

594
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:31,010
You really are something else.

595
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:33,550
Our bodies don't just have healthy cells.

596
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:35,750
They constantly create cancer cells, too,

597
00:47:35,820 --> 00:47:36,850
every single day.

598
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:40,190
I really shouldn't let it get to me.

599
00:47:40,990 --> 00:47:42,890
I feel so much better already.

600
00:47:44,490 --> 00:47:47,130
Okay, from now on, you're my big sister.

601
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:51,300
We're even wearing similar outfits today.

602
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,000
Right. Only the colors are different.

603
00:47:54,140 --> 00:47:56,370
Let's trade to celebrate being sisters.

604
00:47:57,540 --> 00:47:59,780
Your shirt's silk, Momo.

605
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:02,210
I got mine for 25 dollars
at a discount store.

606
00:48:02,380 --> 00:48:05,280
Why so formal? We can be casual now.

607
00:48:05,350 --> 00:48:08,790
I won't call you "Reporter Geum" anymore.
I'll call you Ba Ra.

608
00:49:29,470 --> 00:49:30,930
James, I've been thinking.

609
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:32,440
Looking at how confident Ba Ra is,

610
00:49:33,240 --> 00:49:34,470
do you think she might've had my baby?

611
00:49:34,470 --> 00:49:36,670
You think I haven't thought of that?

612
00:49:37,440 --> 00:49:39,010
But no, the timeline doesn't add up.

613
00:49:39,510 --> 00:49:41,710
Park Sun Woo said she looked like
she was 6 or 7 months along.

614
00:49:41,780 --> 00:49:43,780
She probably just said that
to get you to give up.

615
00:49:44,180 --> 00:49:45,350
Then why did she just disappear?

616
00:49:45,780 --> 00:49:48,020
Because she couldn't bear to see
you and Momo together.

617
00:49:48,850 --> 00:49:50,350
How is she acting toward you?

618
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:52,220
She's different than before.

619
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:55,530
She's a bit cold,
and she's keeping her distance.

620
00:49:56,960 --> 00:49:58,230
It's all because I didn't listen to you...

621
00:49:58,830 --> 00:50:00,660
Do you think it's easy
to get pregnant on the first try?

622
00:50:01,300 --> 00:50:02,830
But if she really did have my baby...

623
00:50:02,970 --> 00:50:04,500
She could have had a miscarriage.

624
00:50:05,240 --> 00:50:06,670
Out of spite, couldn't she have gone...

625
00:50:06,670 --> 00:50:08,970
to one of the guys
who were fawning over her?

626
00:50:09,610 --> 00:50:11,370
Even I had a thing for Reporter Geum.

627
00:50:11,910 --> 00:50:16,310
A Sungwoo Daily reporter meets top players
in politics, finance, and culture.

628
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:17,550
Among them...

629
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:20,350
If she still loved you...

630
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:23,090
or was pregnant with your baby,
she would've come to you.

631
00:50:23,290 --> 00:50:24,350
Why would she go to Director Shin?

632
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:28,530
Don't jump to conclusions.
I'll meet with Reporter Geum and find out.

633
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:30,960
She'll be discharged
right after her MRI, won't she?

634
00:50:31,830 --> 00:50:33,360
She's not going to disappear again,
is she?

635
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:36,070
If she meant to, she would've gone
to another hospital in the first place.

636
00:50:47,140 --> 00:50:48,140
Mom.

637
00:50:49,250 --> 00:50:50,250
Dad.

638
00:50:51,280 --> 00:50:52,280
My little sister.

639
00:50:53,820 --> 00:50:55,890
Our family of four was all together.

640
00:51:02,190 --> 00:51:03,190
Mom.

641
00:51:10,370 --> 00:51:11,570
Goodbye,

642
00:51:12,870 --> 00:51:13,870
Geum Ba Ra.

643
00:51:35,390 --> 00:51:37,390
I miss Oiji and Pickles.

644
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:42,300
(Artist Paul Kim)

645
00:51:46,100 --> 00:51:47,200
Mr. Kim.

646
00:51:47,200 --> 00:51:49,840
Hello. It must be late in Korea, right?

647
00:51:49,970 --> 00:51:52,840
I've still got a while before I turn in.
Are you overseas again?

648
00:51:53,410 --> 00:51:54,410
Yes.

649
00:51:55,780 --> 00:51:57,450
I got curious and searched online,

650
00:51:57,950 --> 00:52:00,320
and an article about
Momo's separation popped up.

651
00:52:00,950 --> 00:52:02,150
I was just wondering if it's true.

652
00:52:02,990 --> 00:52:04,620
I didn't feel comfortable
asking them myself.

653
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:06,520
Yes, it's true.

654
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:08,160
What's the issue?

655
00:52:08,630 --> 00:52:13,300
It seems they just naturally drifted apart
after her last miscarriage.

656
00:52:15,870 --> 00:52:17,100
I feel somewhat responsible.

657
00:52:17,230 --> 00:52:20,670
Why would you feel responsible?
That goes for me, too.

658
00:52:20,900 --> 00:52:23,010
They say only the couple truly knows
what goes on in a marriage.

659
00:52:24,410 --> 00:52:26,110
Let me treat you to a meal
when I get back to Korea.

660
00:52:26,410 --> 00:52:27,940
With Reporter Geum Ba Ra
from Sungwoo Daily.

661
00:52:28,780 --> 00:52:29,950
You know Reporter Geum, don't you?

662
00:52:31,280 --> 00:52:32,780
Are you close? With Reporter Geum Ba Ra?

663
00:52:33,220 --> 00:52:34,220
Yes.

664
00:52:34,580 --> 00:52:37,420
I asked her to check in on my place
every now and then before I left,

665
00:52:38,190 --> 00:52:39,320
but it turns out
she took a leave of absence.

666
00:52:41,060 --> 00:52:42,690
When was the last time you saw her?

667
00:52:51,170 --> 00:52:52,540
I have no choice.

668
00:52:53,900 --> 00:52:55,310
My little sister, Momo,

669
00:52:55,970 --> 00:52:59,010
was a truly good soul who despised evil.

670
00:53:00,410 --> 00:53:02,010
But into her angelic body...

671
00:53:02,810 --> 00:53:04,510
went the brain of Kim Jin Ju.

672
00:53:05,780 --> 00:53:08,380
Can you imagine how horrifying
and agonizing it must be for her soul?

673
00:53:10,090 --> 00:53:11,750
I will give up my own body.

674
00:53:12,820 --> 00:53:13,820
To me...

675
00:53:14,960 --> 00:53:16,790
my sister is more important.

676
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:53,200
Reporter Geum wasn't pregnant.

677
00:53:53,330 --> 00:53:54,930
Either that, or Park Sun Woo was wrong.

678
00:53:56,270 --> 00:53:58,030
I just got off the phone with Paul Kim,

679
00:53:58,530 --> 00:54:01,070
and he said Ba Ra was house-sitting
for him in Yangpyeong.

680
00:54:34,170 --> 00:54:35,540
She also looked
after a colleague's grandmother...

681
00:54:35,540 --> 00:54:36,710
who was stationed overseas.

682
00:54:36,970 --> 00:54:39,240
Paul Kim could've been mistaken, you know.

683
00:54:39,310 --> 00:54:43,210
If you were talking to her face-to-face,
couldn't you tell if she's pregnant?

684
00:54:43,510 --> 00:54:44,810
Maybe not in the early stages, sure.

685
00:54:47,080 --> 00:54:49,950
She was probably upset and said that
just to get under your skin.

686
00:54:51,490 --> 00:54:54,060
If her MRI comes back clear,
she'll probably go straight to Yangpyeong.

687
00:54:54,520 --> 00:54:56,590
You have to stop her, get on your knees,
do whatever it takes.

688
00:54:57,760 --> 00:55:01,100
It's also possible she showed up
since your separation article gave hope.

689
00:55:05,470 --> 00:55:07,540
My imagination was running wild too.

690
00:55:08,640 --> 00:55:09,970
Anyway, what a relief.

691
00:55:23,990 --> 00:55:26,260
(Nua General Hospital)

692
00:55:54,320 --> 00:55:55,650
Has Geum Ba Ra been discharged?

693
00:55:56,620 --> 00:55:58,650
She's one of the Director's patients,
so we wouldn't know.

694
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:03,630
He isn't seeing patients today.

695
00:56:03,630 --> 00:56:05,530
He might be at a conference.

696
00:56:07,660 --> 00:56:10,930
The Director said Geum Ba Ra had an MRI.
Did she have it done?

697
00:56:11,170 --> 00:56:12,670
We have no way of knowing.

698
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:14,300
Why not?

699
00:56:15,100 --> 00:56:16,240
There's no record of it.

700
00:56:27,220 --> 00:56:30,020
The phone you are calling is turned off.
Please leave a message...

701
00:56:30,020 --> 00:56:31,550
(Ju Shin)

702
00:56:35,990 --> 00:56:37,490
(Ba Ra)

703
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:43,230
The phone you are calling is turned off.
Please leave a message after the tone.

704
00:56:43,870 --> 00:56:44,870
(Ba Ra)

705
00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:48,140
What's with both of them?

706
00:57:38,520 --> 00:57:39,520
Welcome, sir.

707
00:57:41,190 --> 00:57:42,990
Is this the one? The new model?

708
00:57:43,130 --> 00:57:44,190
Yes, it is.

709
00:57:46,200 --> 00:57:47,530
Can I get you something to drink?

710
00:57:47,900 --> 00:57:50,300
- An iced Americano.
- An iced Americano?

711
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:51,800
Yes.

712
00:57:53,100 --> 00:57:55,570
- If I order one, how long is the wait?
- It's a three-month wait.

713
00:57:55,710 --> 00:57:56,710
Really? That long?

714
00:57:59,380 --> 00:58:00,740
Is there any way to get it sooner?

715
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:45,880
I need Paul Kim's Yangpyeong address.

716
01:00:46,010 --> 01:00:47,010
You're going there?

717
01:00:47,180 --> 01:00:49,550
- Yes.
- It's no use. We were...

718
01:00:50,780 --> 01:00:52,080
You're a step too late.

719
01:00:52,850 --> 01:00:55,020
Has Director Shin ever
turned his phone off and gone MIA?

720
01:00:57,020 --> 01:00:59,820
The whole MRI thing
could've just been a ploy.

721
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:01,920
Just to keep her at the hospital.

722
01:01:03,560 --> 01:01:05,060
Looks like the two of them
left the country.

723
01:01:09,900 --> 01:01:12,570
I really don't think
you two are meant to be.

724
01:01:13,340 --> 01:01:14,340
Just let her go.

725
01:01:15,770 --> 01:01:18,070
(Momo)

726
01:01:20,440 --> 01:01:22,240
The phone you are calling is turned off.

727
01:01:22,240 --> 01:01:24,650
Please leave your message after the tone.

728
01:01:25,450 --> 01:01:29,090
That brat. Her father has stomach cancer.

729
01:01:32,920 --> 01:01:34,690
- Samhap.
- You brought takeout?

730
01:01:34,690 --> 01:01:37,230
Yes, from the manager's favorite spot
in Mokpo.

731
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:39,660
- I can't eat this.
- Me neither.

732
01:01:39,730 --> 01:01:40,730
Then why did you get it?

733
01:01:41,700 --> 01:01:43,530
I can barely breathe just from the smell.

734
01:01:44,030 --> 01:01:45,300
It's a miracle cure for constipation.

735
01:01:45,300 --> 01:01:47,000
My mom swears by it.

736
01:01:47,500 --> 01:01:49,910
- But still...
- I'm serious.

737
01:01:50,470 --> 01:01:52,610
This is to help with your constipation.

738
01:01:54,940 --> 01:01:56,180
And I'll eat it with you.

739
01:02:03,250 --> 01:02:05,890
- What about your mom?
- My mom has plans most nights.

740
01:02:14,730 --> 01:02:15,730
Just pinch your nose.

741
01:02:18,370 --> 01:02:19,370
Go on, eat up.

742
01:02:19,700 --> 01:02:20,700
Together.

743
01:02:53,500 --> 01:02:55,440
How can this even be considered food?

744
01:02:55,810 --> 01:02:58,240
We probably need to eat seven pieces
for it to work, right?

745
01:02:59,880 --> 01:03:01,440
Even I'm eating it,
and I'm not even constipated.

746
01:03:04,680 --> 01:03:06,280
You're not just doing this to be nice.

747
01:03:06,680 --> 01:03:09,050
I haven't done anything to deserve this,
have I, Momo?

748
01:03:10,950 --> 01:03:14,360
My mom says it also clears up your skin.

749
01:03:14,520 --> 01:03:15,660
My skin is clear.

750
01:03:16,230 --> 01:03:17,860
Just close your eyes and do it.

751
01:03:18,260 --> 01:03:19,960
I'm going to eat seven pieces
right along with you.

752
01:03:23,100 --> 01:03:24,370
Alright, fine.
Since you went to all this trouble.

753
01:03:25,030 --> 01:03:26,040
Exactly.

754
01:03:39,180 --> 01:03:40,180
I, too,

755
01:03:40,650 --> 01:03:42,650
can do anything for my little sister.

756
01:04:16,120 --> 01:04:17,120
You did great.

757
01:04:18,890 --> 01:04:20,690
Jin Ju...

758
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:23,330
Not yet.

759
01:04:44,750 --> 01:04:47,080
She really needs to be taught a lesson.
She really does.

760
01:04:47,820 --> 01:04:49,850
She must have seen my missed calls.

761
01:05:02,670 --> 01:05:03,670
What?

762
01:05:04,930 --> 01:05:06,170
Was Ba Ra discharged?

763
01:05:07,470 --> 01:05:09,540
- No.
- Then what?

764
01:05:10,510 --> 01:05:11,710
She had a brain hemorrhage.

765
01:05:13,080 --> 01:05:14,080
A brain hemorrhage?

766
01:05:16,980 --> 01:05:17,980
And?

767
01:05:19,450 --> 01:05:21,550
- We did emergency surgery.
- You did it yourself?

768
01:05:22,890 --> 01:05:25,020
- When?
- The day before yesterday.

769
01:05:25,350 --> 01:05:26,660
Then why didn't you tell me?

770
01:05:27,220 --> 01:05:28,220
How is she?

771
01:05:30,060 --> 01:05:32,160
- How is she?
- It's only been a day.

772
01:05:33,330 --> 01:05:34,400
She's in the recovery room now.

773
01:05:36,630 --> 01:05:38,100
Then why don't the nurses know anything?

774
01:05:38,230 --> 01:05:39,340
It's what Ba Ra wanted.

775
01:05:41,040 --> 01:05:42,370
She doesn't want people to know.

776
01:05:43,270 --> 01:05:44,670
You even had your phone off.

777
01:05:45,770 --> 01:05:46,780
How was I...

778
01:05:48,410 --> 01:05:49,910
supposed to know
I'd be operating on Ba Ra?

779
01:05:56,950 --> 01:05:58,950
(Ready for surgery)

780
01:05:59,050 --> 01:06:00,060
I have to go into surgery.

781
01:06:02,760 --> 01:06:04,030
Let me see her, just for a second.

782
01:06:19,540 --> 01:06:20,540
Ba Ra.

783
01:06:21,380 --> 01:06:24,680
Were you in so much pain that
a vessel in your brain burst?

784
01:06:26,120 --> 01:06:28,150
Please recover without any complications.

785
01:06:29,020 --> 01:06:30,820
I'm going to stay by your side forever.

786
01:06:39,700 --> 01:06:40,700
Kim...

787
01:06:44,070 --> 01:06:45,330
Jin Ju.

788
01:06:52,740 --> 01:06:54,080
Is there anyone at all we can call?

789
01:06:58,210 --> 01:06:59,350
I'll try.

790
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:02,850
Wait, you can't do the surgery
without a guardian's consent?

791
01:07:09,220 --> 01:07:11,160
The phone you are calling is turned off.

792
01:07:11,230 --> 01:07:12,960
Please leave a message after the tone.

793
01:07:13,500 --> 01:07:14,730
It's off.

794
01:07:15,460 --> 01:07:16,600
You know...

795
01:07:17,300 --> 01:07:19,030
The director here should know her.

796
01:07:19,870 --> 01:07:22,970
Her name's Geum Ba Ra.
She's a reporter for the Sungwoo Daily.

797
01:07:23,410 --> 01:07:26,310
He says he'll ask Geum Ba Ra
to sign the surgical consent form.

798
01:07:26,580 --> 01:07:27,580
And it hasn't metastasized?

799
01:07:28,010 --> 01:07:29,010
That's right.

800
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:33,350
- His registration number.
- It's 6663256.

801
01:07:33,520 --> 01:07:35,350
The phone you are calling is turned off...

802
01:07:36,550 --> 01:07:37,890
That brat...

803
01:07:38,450 --> 01:07:40,190
Her father has stomach cancer.

804
01:07:41,260 --> 01:07:43,790
Don't tell me she ran off again.

805
01:07:44,760 --> 01:07:48,460
Even if she did, her face is famous.
How hard can it be to find her?

806
01:07:55,740 --> 01:07:57,440
What kind of patients
do you usually look after?

807
01:07:58,740 --> 01:08:00,310
Post-op patients, mostly.

808
01:08:00,310 --> 01:08:02,640
For stage one,
you have nothing to worry about.

809
01:08:04,550 --> 01:08:06,650
When can I eat after the surgery?

810
01:08:18,030 --> 01:08:20,830
(Move her tomorrow morning.)

811
01:08:31,140 --> 01:08:32,170
Watch this when you're ready.

812
01:08:57,370 --> 01:08:58,370
Momo.

813
01:08:59,540 --> 01:09:00,670
Will this work now?

814
01:09:01,970 --> 01:09:03,010
Will it?

815
01:09:50,950 --> 01:09:52,350
(Patient transport only)

816
01:09:54,690 --> 01:09:55,990
(Counseling for epilepsy patients
and their families)

817
01:10:29,520 --> 01:10:32,060
When can we see her? She must be awake.

818
01:10:32,160 --> 01:10:33,200
It was brain surgery,

819
01:10:33,460 --> 01:10:34,700
so not until she's moved
to a general ward.

820
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:37,670
This is unbelievable.
I mean, at her age, how could this...

821
01:10:38,270 --> 01:10:39,800
It's not like she drank or smoked.

822
01:10:41,170 --> 01:10:43,340
Could her vessels be weak from poor eating
when she was at the orphanage?

823
01:10:44,870 --> 01:10:45,870
Mr. Kim Gwang Cheol.

824
01:10:47,040 --> 01:10:48,080
Try to open your eyes.

825
01:10:49,880 --> 01:10:51,680
Just you try running off again.

826
01:10:53,050 --> 01:10:54,820
I'll find you if you do.

827
01:10:55,480 --> 01:10:56,520
Mr. Kim Gwang Cheol?

828
01:10:59,190 --> 01:11:01,120
Your surgery went well.

829
01:11:30,650 --> 01:11:31,650
Did she...

830
01:11:32,450 --> 01:11:33,920
go on a trip or something?

831
01:12:07,320 --> 01:12:09,420
(Cashier's check)

832
01:12:18,130 --> 01:12:20,740
To be honest,
you're the one I find most intimidating.

833
01:12:20,870 --> 01:12:23,240
Well, don't be.
You can be comfortable with me.

834
01:12:26,440 --> 01:12:28,110
It's not that I don't trust you,
Director Shin.

835
01:12:37,220 --> 01:12:38,420
Move her to the 12th floor.

836
01:12:38,690 --> 01:12:39,690
Yes, sir.

837
01:12:48,330 --> 01:12:50,230
- Nua General Hospital.
- Yes, sir.

838
01:12:53,370 --> 01:12:54,640
(Neurosurgery Director's Office)

839
01:12:54,840 --> 01:12:55,840
How's Ba Ra?

840
01:13:02,810 --> 01:13:03,810
Brain-dead?

841
01:13:09,480 --> 01:13:10,490
How could this...

842
01:13:12,220 --> 01:13:13,490
You're the one who operated.

843
01:13:18,260 --> 01:13:19,260
What now?

844
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:24,400
- There's nothing I can do.
- What do you mean, nothing?

845
01:13:25,900 --> 01:13:28,300
You have to find a way, whatever it takes.

846
01:13:30,140 --> 01:13:31,140
Shin Ju Shin.

847
01:13:32,870 --> 01:13:35,080
You have to make her wake up.

848
01:13:38,550 --> 01:13:39,550
You think I haven't tried everything?

849
01:13:40,480 --> 01:13:41,480
Then, operate again.

850
01:13:44,250 --> 01:13:45,250
You crazy bastard.

851
01:13:46,090 --> 01:13:47,220
After everything, you did this to Ba Ra...

852
01:13:48,190 --> 01:13:49,190
This is it?

853
01:13:54,300 --> 01:13:55,300
Go see her for yourself.

854
01:14:43,780 --> 01:14:44,780
Ba Ra.

855
01:14:47,920 --> 01:14:49,020
This can't be happening.

856
01:14:57,760 --> 01:14:59,900
Do something. Don't just stand there.

857
01:15:04,700 --> 01:15:07,170
Ba Ra. Can you hear me?

858
01:15:09,600 --> 01:15:10,610
It's me, Ha Yong Joong.

859
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:12,240
Geum Ba Ra.

860
01:15:19,250 --> 01:15:20,420
If you can hear me, squeeze my hand.

861
01:15:21,480 --> 01:15:22,480
Come on.

862
01:15:23,450 --> 01:15:24,450
It's me.

863
01:15:28,860 --> 01:15:30,660
Geum Ba Ra, you're stronger than anyone.

864
01:15:32,090 --> 01:15:33,090
Please.

865
01:15:44,810 --> 01:15:47,040
Hey. Are you just going to stand there?

866
01:15:49,510 --> 01:15:51,180
I'm moving her to Seoltap Hospital.

867
01:15:51,480 --> 01:15:52,480
It's no use.

868
01:15:52,480 --> 01:15:54,480
No use? After what you've done to her?

869
01:15:55,120 --> 01:15:56,950
You should've had Dr. Kim Jun Oh
do the surgery.

870
01:16:02,620 --> 01:16:04,490
Get Seoltap Hospital on the line.
It's an emergency.

871
01:16:04,590 --> 01:16:06,490
You want to drag her between hospitals
just to open up her skull again?

872
01:16:06,930 --> 01:16:08,630
One more surgery
and she'll die on the table.

873
01:16:17,910 --> 01:16:18,910
Then take responsibility.

874
01:16:24,950 --> 01:16:26,650
If you're human,
take responsibility for this, you bastard!

875
01:16:27,480 --> 01:16:28,480
Hey!

876
01:16:49,470 --> 01:16:51,340
I've made some beef porridge for you.

877
01:16:51,810 --> 01:16:54,880
I think I'm ready for a proper meal now.

878
01:17:36,420 --> 01:17:38,550
- Oh, yes...
- I'm Geum Ba Ra.

879
01:17:38,620 --> 01:17:40,460
That's right. You have a unique name.

880
01:17:42,960 --> 01:17:45,090
Why did you give up on me?
I'm your daughter.

881
01:17:49,900 --> 01:17:52,200
Shouldn't a mother recognize
her own child?

882
01:17:54,970 --> 01:17:56,400
After all the pain
of giving birth to me...

883
01:17:57,770 --> 01:17:58,770
(Director Shin)

884
01:18:08,120 --> 01:18:09,250
Yes, Director Shin.

885
01:18:17,460 --> 01:18:20,030
(Nua General Hospital)

886
01:18:48,820 --> 01:18:50,660
I never thought it would come to this.

887
01:20:00,160 --> 01:20:03,100
(Doctor Shin)

888
01:20:03,200 --> 01:20:04,830
You're supposed to wear a swimsuit
at the pool.

889
01:20:04,830 --> 01:20:06,530
Jin Ju's father came to see me.

890
01:20:06,630 --> 01:20:08,440
That looked like Geum Ba Ra, the reporter.

891
01:20:08,440 --> 01:20:10,370
Was she in a car accident or something?

892
01:20:10,440 --> 01:20:12,170
Is the owner of this house...

893
01:20:12,710 --> 01:20:14,080
still not out of the hospital yet?

894
01:20:14,080 --> 01:20:15,580
She's friends with my daughter.

895
01:20:15,640 --> 01:20:16,640
But you haven't heard?

896
01:20:17,280 --> 01:20:18,610
She passed away a little while ago.

897
01:20:20,350 --> 01:20:21,680
There won't be a funeral
before the burial.

898
01:20:21,880 --> 01:20:23,350
She was in the prime of her life.

899
01:20:23,420 --> 01:20:24,850
Your Daddy...

900
01:20:24,990 --> 01:20:26,450
cried so much today.

901
01:20:26,450 --> 01:20:27,560
Sounds just like Kim Jin Ju.

902
01:20:28,160 --> 01:20:29,790
It's true what they say,
people don't change.

903
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:34,200
I'm not sure I'm supposed to address you.

904
01:20:34,200 --> 01:20:36,000
Let me get straight to the point.

905
01:20:36,100 --> 01:20:38,970
(Nua General Hospital)

906
01:20:39,030 --> 01:20:40,400
There's a dead body here!

907
01:20:40,740 --> 01:20:43,240
I think it's a patient
we operated on recently.

908
01:20:43,300 --> 01:20:44,670
- And the Director isn't here?
- No, sir.

909
01:20:44,870 --> 01:20:46,140
You are not going to believe this.

910
01:20:46,140 --> 01:20:47,880
I'm on my way to your house,
so run there...

911
01:20:47,880 --> 01:20:48,880
at the speed of light.
